item.title: Boschman "History Will Be Made" NHL Parody
item.description:
Boschman "History Will Be Made" NHL Parody
In 1991, The NJ Devils were up 3 games to 2 over the Pittsburgh Penguins in the 1st round. The Devils came back from 3 goals down and would have tied Game 6 (AT HOME) with this goal by Laurie Boschman. However, it was waved off by Referee Bill McCreary even though replays showed it hit Boschman's stick AFTER it hit his skate. The score stood and the Devils lost the game (and the series) 4 - 3. Pens' fans can talk about "The Save" all they want, but we talk about getting legitimately hosed. Maybe "Super" Mario Lemieux would have never won his 1st Cup if the NHL had Instant Replay in the 1991 Playoffs.

item.title: Kate Gosselin on DWTS Week 3
item.description:
Kate Gosselin on DWTS Week 3
Kate made it through the first elimination of DWTS and is back to perform the Pasa Doble. This week included a challenge issued to all contestants to tell a story with their dance and Kate decided to go with the love-hate relationship with the paparazzi... although many speculated it would be the love-hate relationship with Jon. This is an interesting song choice since she was on the Leno show a few months ago saying paparazzi was her favorite song and even sung a little bit of it. In the same show she also said how much she would love to be on Dancing With The Stars. And here she is making that combo happen. Will she be cut in the elimination or will she be back to dance yet again? I actually thought she looked better than last week - but maybe that's just because the last dance was almost painful to watch. The technical dancing seemed a bit mundane, but I don't know much about dancing. The look on her face when the judges were giving feedback was priceless because she certainly looked like she was expecting rave reviews. This video is just the taped piece, dancing, judges comments, and judges scores. Watch for another video that highlights the other parts of the show with Kate in them.
